org.midica.file

Class SoundfontParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.midica.file.SoundfontParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IParser

    public class SoundfontParser
extends java.lang.Object
implements IParser

    This class is used in order to load a user-defined soundfont file.

    It’s also used for retrieving information from the currently loaded (or standard) soundfont.

      • makeNumberRangeString

        private static java.lang.String makeNumberRangeString(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> list)

        Transforms a list of numbers into a String describing these numbers in ranges.

        E.g. the list (2, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 11, 15, 16, 17, 20) would result in the string 2, 5-9, 11, 15-17, 20

        Parameters:
        list - Sorted list of numbers.
        Returns:
        Compressed but still human-readable range string.
